name: DIVINE COMEDY | CANTO I
description:
"DANTE LOST IN A DARK WOOD"

The poem begins on the night of Maundy Thursday on March 24, 1300, shortly before dawn of Good Friday. Dante, is thirty-five years old. The poet finds himself lost in a dark wood, astray from the "straight way" of salvation...
